text.section:
On the certificate of candidacy form prescribed by the State Board, the candidate shall specify:
the office, including, if applicable, the party, district, and circuit to which the candidacy relates;
the year of the election;
the name of the individual filing the certificate;
the address on the statewide voter registration list or the current address of that individual;
a statement that the individual satisfies the requirements of law for candidacy for the office for which the certificate is being filed; and
any information requested by the State Board to verify the accuracy of the information provided by the individual under this subsection.
